{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Grease a rectangular baking tin (26 x 16 x 3.5 cm). Line the base and sides of tin with baking paper, allowing a 5 cm overhang for easy removal later. Set baking tin aside.","Place macadamias and pistachios into mixing bowl and chop <b>2 sec\/speed 5<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Place apricots and glacé cherries or dried cranberries into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>. Transfer into bowl with the nuts and set aside.","Place chocolate into mixing bowl and grate <b>4 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then melt <b>3 min\/37°C\/speed 1<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then melt for a further <b>4 min\/37°C\/speed 1<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula again and melt for a further <b>2-4 min\/37°C\/speed 1<b>, or until chocolate has fully melted.","Add Turkish delight pieces, marshmallows pieces, desiccated coconut and reserved apricot and nut mixture and combine <b>15 sec\/\/speed 2<b>, or until combined.","Place a large bowl onto mixing bowl lid, then weigh Rice Bubbles into it. Transfer white chocolate mixture into large bowl with the Rice Bubbles and combine until well-coated.","Pour mixture into prepared baking tin and press down firmly to smooth and compact. Place tin into refrigerator to set for 2 hours or until firm. Once set, cut into approx. 20 pieces and serve or transfer into a sealable container and store in refrigerator until ready to use."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["butter, for greasing","40 g roasted unsalted macadamia nuts","30 g roasted unsalted pistachio nuts","50 g dried apricots","50 g glacé cherries","500 g white chocolate, broken into pieces","80 g Turkish delight, cut into cubes (1 cm)","50 g marshmallow, cut into cubes (1 cm)","20 g desiccated coconut","80 g Rice Bubbles"]}],"id":"r92422","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-7Ue5KpVXW2E\/XZaojImVlXI\/AAAAAAAAhLI\/RLAzi05iTZYig-BMqzoAL6HeuL